Distribution:
Most of the specimens of 

Bothroponera granosa

were collected from South Africa, including the Eastern Cape and KwaZulu-Natal Provinces. They were also collected from the Cape of Good Hope (
Roger, 1860
), Natal area (
Forel, 1901
) and from Cape Knysna and Cape Majuba Nek areas (
Arnold, 1926
). Some specimens were collected from Victoria Falls, Zimbabwe (
Arnold, 1926
).
